<h4> <span class="mw-headline" id="Cryptography_can_do_more">Cryptography can do more</span></h4>
<ul>
<li><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Digital_signatures">Digital signatures</a></li>
<li>Anonymous communication <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mix_net">Mix Net</a></li>
<li>Anonymous <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Digital_cash">digital cash</a></li>
<li>Pseudonymous <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://bitcoin.org/bitcoin.pdf">digital cash</a></li>
</ul>
<h4> <span class="mw-headline" id="Protocols">Protocols</span></h4>
<ul>
<li>Elections</li>
<li>Private auctions</li>
</ul>
<p>Anything that can be done with a trusted authority can also be done without. Instead of talking to the central authority the parties (voters) talk to each other using a protocol in a way that at the end the protocol reveals the outcome of the election without revealing the individual inputs</p>
<h4> <span class="mw-headline" id="Crypto_Magic">Crypto Magic</span></h4>
<ul>
<li>Privately outsourcing computation <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Verifiable_computing">Verifiable computing</a></li>
<li><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Zero-knowledge_proof">Zero knowledge proof</a></li>
</ul>
<h4> <span class="mw-headline" id="A_rigorous_science">A rigorous science</span></h4>
<p>The three steps in cryptography:
<ul><li>Precisely define threat model
</li><li>Propose a construction
</li><li>Prove that breaking construction under threat model will solve an underlying hard problem</p>
</li></ul>

<h4> <span class="mw-headline" id="Thm">Thm</span></h4>
<p>Thm means theorem.</p>

